         i'm 99.9% sure that the "4 pets on a mob" is 4 attacking, literally swinging, at the same time.  so unless you happen to have more then 4 pets with the same haste, the same delay, and all of them attack at the same exact time....</P><P>i've seen logs of more then 4 pets swinging on a mob.  so it is 4 pets attacking at once...not more then 4 attacking.</P><P>and in exp groups breaking up DoTs with several people is nice.  Everyone has a DoT they cast...pull about 4-8 mobs (1 necro can do 4 at once...5 necro's and a shaman can easily hold 4-8), everyone casts 1 DoT...mobs all die and everyone is still FM.  making it really easy to chain pull 4+ mobs at a time.  </P><P>would it be 100 times easier and more effective if DoTs stacked?  yep.  does it work despite the fact that they don't stack? yep.</P><P><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu<BR>Inverse Logic</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
